==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Concamerate
<hw>Con*cam"er*ate</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧n*k⟦acr⟧m"⟦etil⟧r*⟦amac⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>concameratus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>concamerare</ets> to arch over. See <er>Camber</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To arch over; to vault.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of the upper beak an inch and a half consisteth of one
<qex>concamerated</qex> bone.</q> <rj><qau>Grew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To divide into chambers or cells.</def>
<rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concameration</ent>⟦br⟧
